INSERT INTO `webnews` (`id`, `title`, `slug`, `image`, `text`, `author`) VALUES
(1, 'A STRUGGLE FOR MOMENTUM: STUDENT BODY FORMATION', 'a-struggle-for-momentum-student-body-formation', '', 'The humongous task of incepting a student body was undertaken by Ex-Director nominated SAC convener, Soham Ghosh. The rudimentary idea for the same sprouted way before that. In 2010, an ex CC of MM, Samik Ghoshal and the other Directors’ nominees, Babaji Chikkam, Nishant Nihar and Anand Babu envisioned a centralised students’ body that would cater to the needs of the students and help in the administrative process.\r\n\r\n A heavy buzzing and circulations of this proposal have been going in the institute but its roots lay elsewhere, interestingly. In actuality, it is a nationwide and worldwide concept. Basically, it is a student’s union or organization present in many colleges, universities, and high schools that cater to a particular need of the same, administrative or otherwise. In higher education, the students'' union is often accorded its own building on the campus, dedicated to social, organizational activities, representation and academic support of the membership. Akhil Bhartiya Vidyarthi Parishad, National Students Union of India, Students Federation of India, All India Students Association & All India Democratic Students Organisation are some of the prominent Students'' Organisations in India.\r\n\r\nThere have been some manifestations in NIT-R to form a student body catering to the present needs of the institute. The student body here refers to a mediator between the general authority that comprises of the assigned officials in the administration and the students at the very ground level. And that, it should portray itself as an authority itself so as to gain the trust of students as well as the officials. Consider the following example. If a student needs to perform a late registration, a series of steps need to be followed such as getting a late fine form from academic office, getting the signature from his/her department HOD and faculty advisor, entailing within it myriad hassles.  Furthermore, there are other numerous loopholes in the present student benefitting bodies such as SAC, like the fact that there are several elected representatives who do not perform competently or don’t do a single task in their entire tenure but do get certificates on the Foundation Day. There is no proper mechanism in place to deal with this matter efficiently. Having a student body will help smoothen out many administrative hassles and ensure the proper functioning of other student bodies like SAC.\r\n\r\nA basic constitution was drafted by Soham Ghosh in 2015 as a manifestation for the director, SAC post which basically consisted of some ground level requirements, namely:\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n It should consist of around 15 members with some prerequisites such as:\r\nThe student should have a CGPA of 7 or above.\r\nShould be or have been an active member of SAC or HMC.\r\nShould be a 3rd or 4th year.\r\n       \r\n\r\nAlthough no direct intervention is mentioned, recommendations would be duly welcomed by the authorities.\r\n        \r\n\r\nThe body would be advisory in nature which will communicate the problems of the masses to the authorities. It would also look into trivial matters before it passes to ISDC (Institute Standing Disciplinary Committee) of Senate with an objective of resolving it internally.\r\n \r\n\r\nUnlike the case of SAC, there would be an impeachment procedure to remove people if they fail to meet the standards.\r\n \r\n\r\nThese ideas were discussed with the then Director, Prof. S.K. Sarangi and Dean of student welfare, Prof. K.C. Pati and to some extent they were reshaped. New points added to the prerequisites for the constituent body were:\r\n\r\nSophomores should also be allowed into that body.\r\n \r\n\r\nThe students should not have unscrupulous activities to their name.\r\n \r\n\r\nIn the previous year, there was a poll analysis conducted on the Junta’s opinion on this Student Body and the results were prominently unidirectional.\r\n\r\n88% of the populace were in the support of it and wanted it to come into action as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThe last year’s draft of Soham Ghosh proved to be a milestone in the path to this idea and created some momentum. In a recent interaction with MM, he said:\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n“It gained momentum the last year because I went forward and presented a draft formulated by my predecessor, presented it to the director and kept in touch with him. The Director alone cannot approve a student body. It has to go through a lot of other tiers. I directly went to the tertiary tier because I knew that the others would refer me to him. Anyhow, director loved the idea and was receptive to it. I interacted with Prof. K.C.Pati and presented the draft by the end of summer. Substantial progress was not made after that.”\r\n \r\n\r\nClearing up the air, ex- Dean, Student Welfare, Prof. K.C.Pati, said that:\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n“The idea was taken up in the HOD meeting but was referred to the next meeting because of some reasons. And in the last two months, we’ve been busy due to other problems here. Thus, it would be better to take up this issue to the present dean, Prof. D.R.K. Padhi and there are no such major stumbles to it.”', 'dhruthi'),
(2, 'A STRUGGLE FOR MOMENTUM: STUDENT BODY FORMATION', 'a-struggle-for-momentum-student-body-formation', '', 'The humongous task of incepting a student body was undertaken by Ex-Director nominated SAC convener, Soham Ghosh. The rudimentary idea for the same sprouted way before that. In 2010, an ex CC of MM, Samik Ghoshal and the other Directors’ nominees, Babaji Chikkam, Nishant Nihar and Anand Babu envisioned a centralised students’ body that would cater to the needs of the students and help in the administrative process.\r\n\r\n A heavy buzzing and circulations of this proposal have been going in the institute but its roots lay elsewhere, interestingly. In actuality, it is a nationwide and worldwide concept. Basically, it is a student’s union or organization present in many colleges, universities, and high schools that cater to a particular need of the same, administrative or otherwise. In higher education, the students'' union is often accorded its own building on the campus, dedicated to social, organizational activities, representation and academic support of the membership. Akhil Bhartiya Vidyarthi Parishad, National Students Union of India, Students Federation of India, All India Students Association & All India Democratic Students Organisation are some of the prominent Students'' Organisations in India.\r\n\r\nThere have been some manifestations in NIT-R to form a student body catering to the present needs of the institute. The student body here refers to a mediator between the general authority that comprises of the assigned officials in the administration and the students at the very ground level. And that, it should portray itself as an authority itself so as to gain the trust of students as well as the officials. Consider the following example. If a student needs to perform a late registration, a series of steps need to be followed such as getting a late fine form from academic office, getting the signature from his/her department HOD and faculty advisor